        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-10-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-10-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="800" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d800">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.24/10–2645: Airgram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the Dominican Republic</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">McGurk</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-10-26">October 26,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>A–348. ReDeptCirInstruction Sept. 11, 1945, and enclosure.<note n="24" xml:id="d800fn24">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_5">p. 5</ref>.</note> War Dept
                    has submitted program designed to equip suitable initial ground force units
                    envisaged in staff conversations.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
